  "doc_id": "55178",
  "text": "Asunaprevir and daclatasvir are mainly eliminated through liver. Therefore, this combination therapy for 24 weeks is not contraindicated in patients with severe renal impairment, including HCV GT-1 patients with hemodialysis and was highly effective and well tolerated [CITATION_1] .",
